This is the VTA+ Skill for Smart Home products, if you have any questions or difficulties, do not hesitate to contact us at contactenos@vta.co

You can ask Alexa to turn the light on, off, or change the intensity. There's no need to open multiple apps to control everything or do it manually - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap, or Echo Show. After connecting Alexa to your VTA products in a few easy steps:

(1) Download our "VTA+" app from Android or IOS app store;
(2) Register as a new user in the "VTA+" application if you already have a user, skip this step;
(3) You need to have VTA+ products;
(4) Make the configuration of the products in the VTA+ application and change the name of the devices that will be used in the application;
(5) Download the Amazon "Alexa" app from the Android, IOS app store;
(6) Set up your account in the "Alexa" app;
(7) Then Look for the Skill "VTA+" in the skill category of the "Alexa" application;
(8) Select Activate the "VTA+" skill
(9) Follow the instructions on the page to complete the link;
(10) Once finished close the interface and go to the devices tab.

Now you can enjoy voice control on your smart devices like these:
"Alexa, turn on the kitchen light" 
"Alexa, turn off the kitchen light"
"Alexa, set the intensity to full brightness" 
"Alexa, turn up the brightness of the living room light"
"Alexa, turn on the multi-outlet in the living room" 
"Alexa, turn off the multi-outlet"
"Alexa, set the bedroom light to 20%" 
"Alexa, turn off the bedroom light"

Currently this Skill supports products that are On-Off, or that can be activated or deactivated, however, some others are compatible for certain functions.
